\begin{align*}
    T_1 &= 2\pi \sqrt{\frac{L_1}{g}}, \\
    T_2 &= 2\pi \sqrt{\frac{L_2}{g}}.
\end{align*}

The time taken for one pendulum to gain a complete oscillation on the other is given by the beat period:
\[
    T_{\text{beat}} = \frac{T_1 T_2}{|T_2 - T_1|}
\]

Substitute the expressions for \(T_1\) and \(T_2\) to find \(T_{\text{beat}}\).

\end{document}
```

